The incident comes two months after an officer stationed at the Ocean View police station allegedly shot dead his wife before turning the gun on himself. “Khayelitsha detectives are investigating cases of murder and a death inquest subsequent to a shooting incident that occurred yesterday (Saturday) afternoon at about 2.30pm in Site B, Khayelitsha. “According to information, a 27-year-old police constable stationed at Philippi East Crime Prevention was on duty at the time. “He allegedly shot and fatally wounded a 23-year-old man before shooting himself with his service pistol. “Circumstances surrounding this incident are under investigation,” Police spokesperson Noloyiso Rwexana said. Police and Prisons Civil Rights Union (Popcru) spokesperson Richard Mamabolo said station and unit commanders had to take steps if they saw members were not well, and family members had to report abnormal behaviour. “We have seen numerous suicides among police officers, mostly between the ages of 18 to 35 years old. “This is usually due to post-traumatic stress disorder, work stress and personal circumstances. These are normally the driver of these very tragic incidents,” Mamabolo said. CAPE TIMES